From 552c1c53f29984779b69c7df7a7e84d2bc173f6b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 13:59:59 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: admin RBAC + auth/dashboard bug fixes, merged from two
 independent reviews
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

This combines two independent passes at securing/completing the admin backend,
keeping whichever version of each piece was actually correct after diffing
both against real main and running the full test suite against each change.

Critical bugs fixed:
- auth.service.ts referenced prisma.passwordResetToken, prisma.emailVerificationToken,
  and user.emailVerified with none of them defined in schema.prisma — registration
  and password reset were broken. Added the missing models/field.
- Dashboard's raw SQL queried a snake_case created_at column that doesn't exist
  (fields aren't @map'd, so Prisma generates camelCase createdAt) — the daily
  activity and registrations charts would 500 against a real database.

Security gap fixed (the original ask):
- Every /admin/* controller, plus the admin-only routes on /exercises and
  /contests, only checked JwtAuthGuard, not role. Added RolesGuard + @Roles.
- Suspending/banning a user had no actual effect anywhere — JwtStrategy never
  checked account status, and login() didn't either, so a banned user's
  existing token (and even a fresh login) kept working. Now enforced on
  login and re-checked on every authenticated request.
- Admin accounts can no longer be suspended/banned via the status endpoint,
  or have their own role changed via the new promotion endpoint (self-lockout
  guard).

New capability:
- PATCH /admin/users/:id/role lets an existing admin promote another account
  to ADMIN (or demote back to STUDENT) — previously the only way to get an
  admin account at all was the seed script, with no way to add a second one.

Data integrity fixed:
- admin-content.controller.ts accepted untyped bodies for exercise/contest
  updates. Added proper DTOs.
- The contest-update DTO/service silently dropped question edits — a PUT to
  /admin/content/contests/:id could change metadata but never touch the
  actual questions. Restored, wrapped in a transaction alongside the
  exercise-choice replacement so a partial failure can't leave an exercise
  with zero answer choices.

Coherence with backlog #12 (config should actually apply):
- PlatformSettings (hint penalties, XP per forum post/reply) was stored but
  never read anywhere. Wired into exercise/contest grading and forum
  post/reply creation, with a defensive fallback so a settings-lookup hiccup
  never blocks a submission.

Also included:
- prisma/seed.ts + prisma.config.ts seed hook to bootstrap the first admin
  account, refusing to run without an explicit strong password rather than
  falling back to a hardcoded default.
- Test coverage for every admin service, plus new specs for the two pieces
  that had none before (jwt.strategy's status enforcement, admin-users'
  ban-protection and role-promotion guards). Full suite: 17/17 suites,
  119/119 tests passing (verified against a local Prisma client stub, since
  this sandbox can't reach Prisma's engine CDN to run a real generate).

Note: still run 'npx prisma migrate dev' and 'npx prisma db seed' locally —
this could not be verified against a real Postgres database from here.
